macro_markets.query: What are the most important macroeconomic and stock market news and developments from the past 24 hours? Include major index movements, Fed/central bank news, and significant company earnings or announcements.

items.title: Indian Nifty 50 Surges 4.86% and Sensex 4.48% on US-India Trade Deal
items.summary: Indian stock markets opened sharply higher with Nifty 50 up 4.86% and Sensex up 4.48% following the signing of a trade deal between India and the USA. This marks a significant bullish rally after recent mixed sessions.

items.title: US S&P 500 Hits 7000 Points with 0.33% Gain
items.summary: The US500 index rose to 7000 points on February 3, 2026, gaining 0.33% from the prior session, following a 0.72% increase to 6989 on February 2. Year-to-date performance shows strong growth of over 16%.

items.title: US Non-Farm Payrolls Beat Expectations, Boosting Fed Rate Hike Speculation
items.summary: Stronger-than-expected US job growth in the latest Non-Farm Payrolls data has fueled speculation on Federal Reserve interest rate decisions. The dollar strengthened amid this economic indicator.

items.title: Eurozone Inflation Data Pressures Euro and ECB Policy Outlook
items.summary: Higher-than-expected Eurozone inflation figures are weighing on the euro, prompting expectations of more aggressive action from the European Central Bank. EUR/USD traded lower amid economic stability concerns.

items.title: NASDAQ Composite Closes at 23,592 on February 2
items.summary: The NASDAQ Composite Index ended at 23,592.110 on February 2, 2026, reflecting recent volatility with prior closes around 23,400-23,800 levels.

crypto_news.query: What are the most significant cryptocurrency and blockchain news from the past 24 hours? Include major price movements, regulatory news, and notable project developments.

items.title: Binance Converts $1B SAFU Fund to Bitcoin Reserves
items.summary: Binance announced plans to convert its $1 billion SAFU Fund into Bitcoin within 30 days amid market criticism following the October 2025 crypto crash. The move addresses concerns from community members and investors like Cathy Woods.

items.title: Bitcoin Slumps to 10-Month Low Around $78,000
items.summary: Bitcoin prices have fallen to a 10-month low, hovering above $78,000, amid bearish market sentiment and technical breakdowns like a weekly bear flag. Analysts discuss potential further declines or recovery catalysts.

items.title: UAE-Tied Firm Signs $500M Deal with Trump Crypto Venture
items.summary: A UAE-linked investment firm secretly signed a $500 million deal with the Trump family's cryptocurrency venture just four days before President Trump took office last year, according to the Wall Street Journal.

items.title: Bitcoin Slide Accelerates Amid Inflation Hawk Fears
items.summary: Bitcoin's price decline has intensified due to concerns over inflation hawks rattling crypto markets, contributing to the cryptocurrency's drop to historic lows.

items.title: Analysts Predict Bitcoin Could Reach $1 Million Despite Dip
items.summary: Despite Bitcoin's slump to around $78,000, Bitwise's Head of Research forecasts it could hit $1 million in the next decade, citing ETF flows and institutional adoption from firms like Morgan Stanley and Vanguard.

ai_news.query: What are the most important artificial intelligence and machine learning news and developments from the past 24 hours? Include new model releases, company announcements, research breakthroughs, and industry trends.

items.title: Ai2 Launches Theorizer for Automatic Theory Synthesis from Scientific Papers
items.summary: Ai2 introduced Theorizer, an open-source tool that synthesizes explicit scientific laws from up to 100 papers per query, outputting structured ⟨LAW, SCOPE, EVIDENCE⟩ results with 0.88–0.90 precision. It uses GPT-4.1 for synthesis and runs in 15–30 minutes, improving recall through literature grounding.

items.title: Anthropic Study Reveals AI Assistance Hinders Learning in Async Programming Tasks
items.summary: Anthropic's evaluation showed AI-assisted groups averaged 50% on quizzes versus 67% for no-AI groups, with a 17-point gap (p=0.01), particularly in debugging. AI users finished tasks faster but showed reduced short-term understanding and conceptual comprehension.

items.title: AI Agents Face Rising MCP Vulnerabilities and Security Threats
items.summary: PointGuard AI reported a surge in Model Context Protocol (MCP) exploits allowing credential theft and AI agent takeovers in January 2026. Microsoft's survey found 47% of leaders implementing AI-specific controls amid 32% of incidents involving generative AI.

items.title: Universal Robots Predicts Key Physical AI Advances for 2026
items.summary: Universal Robots forecasts faster robot skill acquisition via intelligent sensors and self-correction, plus more natural human-robot collaboration through AI-driven perception of gestures and context, enabling applications in healthcare, warehouses, and assembly.

items.title: Emerging Autonomous AI Systems Enable Self-Improvement Without Human Supervision
items.summary: New AI paradigms shift to unsupervised learning and advanced neural architectures, allowing systems to adapt, discover patterns, and evolve independently, with applications in manufacturing predictive maintenance and healthcare diagnostics.

items.title: India AI Pre-Summit 2026 Held Today at BVRIT
items.summary: BVRIT hosted a one-day INDIA AI Pre-Summit 2026 on February 3, focusing on preparing students for AI advancements amid centers in AI/ML, robotics, and cognitive sciences.

gaming.query: What are the most notable video game and gaming industry news from the past 24 hours? Include game releases, announcements, esports, and industry developments.

items.title: The Sims 4 Receives Major Base Game Update on February 3rd
items.summary: The Sims 4 base game update introduces new build tools like tapestry objects for lineage history, relationship adjustments, family books, curly hair options, cultural traditions, and new nail designs. All features arrive today, February 3rd, 2026.[4]

items.title: Nintendo Switch Reaches 155 Million Units Sold Milestone
items.summary: Nintendo Switch has now sold over 155 million units, with Switch 2 confirmed as the fastest-selling console in history at 17 million shipped. This positions it ahead of previous records.[5]

items.title: New FIFA Game Announced for Summer 2026 World Cup Release
items.summary: A new FIFA game is set to launch in time for the World Cup this summer, with a full release across all platforms. It is part of the GOG Preservation Program for modern PC compatibility.[5]

items.title: Wave of Superhero Games Confirmed for 2026 Including Wolverine and Spider-Man 3
items.summary: Over 12 superhero games are confirmed for 2026 and beyond, featuring Marvel's Wolverine, Spider-Man 3 for PS6, Invincible VS, and others like Batman Arkham sequel. Highlights include Marvel Tōkon fighting game rumors and delays for titles like Rise of Hydra.[3]

items.title: Indie Gaming Highlights for Week of February 2-8: Jackal and Monster Train 2
items.summary: This week's indie releases spotlight Jackal as a potential Hotline Miami successor, alongside Monster Train 2: Destiny of the Railforged, Demon Dust, and others like HumanitZ and Carmageddon: Rogue Shift.[2]

items.title: Biggest Game Releases Lined Up for February 2026
items.summary: February 2026 features major releases including Mewgenics with cat breeding battles and Resident Evil Requiem revisiting Raccoon City zombies, among other new titles.[1]

tech_news.query: What are the most important technology news and developments from the past 24 hours? Include major product launches, company news, and significant tech industry developments. Exclude AI-specific news.

items.title: Apple's Fiscal Q1 2026 Earnings Beat Expectations with $143.8 Billion Revenue
items.summary: Apple reported fiscal Q1 2026 revenue of $143.8 billion and EPS of $2.84, surpassing consensus estimates of $138.4 billion and $2.67. Evercore ISI removed Apple from its tactical outperform list following the strong results.

items.title: Apple Flags Supply Constraints for Q2 2026 Due to TSMC 3nm Chip Shortages
items.summary: Apple anticipates constraints in fiscal Q2 2026 from limited TSMC 3nm processor supply, driven by strong Q1 demand and capacity limits amid AI accelerator production ramps. CFO noted guidance reflects best estimates of constrained supply.

items.title: Micron Positioned for Growth as AI Memory Demand Shifts Bottleneck from Compute
items.summary: Analysts project Micron benefiting from rising demand for high-bandwidth memory, with Goldman Sachs forecasting $500 billion AI capex in 2026 and TrendForce predicting DRAM prices up 60% and NAND up 38%. This follows Nvidia's GPU dominance.

items.title: Logitech Launches Affordable Gaming Headset with 24-Hour Battery Life
items.summary: Logitech revealed a stylish, budget-friendly gaming headset designed for portable 'chill' use, featuring a 24-hour battery life.

items.title: Two New Affordable DJI Drones Leak Ahead of Potential US Ban Exemption
items.summary: Leaks reveal two budget DJI drones that may avoid the US ban, offering accessible options in the consumer drone market.

items.title: India Offers Zero Taxes to Foreign Cloud Providers Using Local Data Centers Until 2047
items.summary: India incentivizes foreign cloud providers with tax exemptions until 2047, conditional on routing data through Indian data centers to boost local infrastructure.

items.title: Oracle Launches Massive $45-50 Billion Bond and Equity Sale for Cloud Expansion
items.summary: Oracle is raising $45-50 billion through debt and equity this year to build cloud infrastructure capacity amid surging demand.
